Subject: refuse private objects in load/1 and drop data fields from allow-public

The shared load/1 helper returned whatever object id the caller asked
for, including private incidents. Reject the lookup when the object is
not marked public, and strip the data field from successful responses
so the allow-public branch can only ever reveal metadata.

--- a/service/lib/policy_forge/policy_dsl.ex
+++ b/service/lib/policy_forge/policy_dsl.ex
@@ -55,7 +55,8 @@
   defp load(id) do
     case PolicyForge.State.object(id) do
       nil -> %{error: "missing"}
-      obj -> %{decision: "allow", object: obj}
+      %{public: true} = obj -> %{decision: "allow", object: Map.drop(obj, [:data])}
+      _ -> %{error: "policy_scope_denied"}
     end
   end
 end
